parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the motorcycle to stall or shut off while in operation, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents, especially at night when the headlights fail.
The failure of the wiring harness can cause electrical system malfunctions, leading to stalling or shutting off of the motorcycle, which can result in accidents or leave the rider stranded.
Corrosion of the ground wire can cause electrical system malfunctions, leading to stalling or shutting off of the motorcycle, which can result in accidents or leave the rider stranded.
symptoms: Motorcycle engine dies after the starter button is released
headlight fuse removal allows the motorcycle to start and run fine
corrosion of the ground wire pin inside the main wiring connector block.
